After looking at https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-boxes/commit/929848c3be9cd11f1f25f44f982e8e611238fdb5, I've decided to spend some time to debug the possible regression and I have to admit that I'm surprised that the commit itself doesn't cause any breakage and that this whole thing has ever worked in the past.

I've found that the reason of the breakage is because "usb.ids" file is not found. USB_IDS is not automatically filled, and `-Dwith-usb-ids-path` is never set. :-)

Let's go through the interesting findings:
- It's known that libosinfo *depends on* hwdata. Being more specific, on *usb.ids* and *pci.ids* files;
  - It's known to the point Boxes' keeps both files and they're mentioned in the manifest;
- freedesktop-sdk *does* ship pci.ids, bit does *not* ship usb.ids;
  - Please, refer to https://gitlab.com/freedesktop-sdk/freedesktop-sdk/issues/926 in the future;
- libosinfo downloads both files and installs them in `$PKG_DATA_DIR/libosinfo/` if they're not found;
  - But there's neither `wget` as part of freedesktop-sdk nor internet access when building the nightly flatpak;
  - And it's broken in 1.7.0 release;

I'll have to cut a new release Tomorrow morning (due to yet another breakage), which should fix the last bullet.

Regardless, I do believe this series should be considered as the proper fix, at least till https://gitlab.com/freedesktop-sdk/freedesktop-sdk/issues/926 is fixed and then we can drop the shenanigans added here.
